kpi_info.title: period_duration (period_duration)
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: REC_RTP_PACKETS (M803C0)
kpi_info.use: The number of received RTP packets. The actual number of packets can be calculated by multiplying this counter value by 10. UPDATED: When an RTP packet is received from the core network. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REC_RTP_PAYLOAD (M803C1)
kpi_info.use: The RTP payload data received during the measurement interval. Header and padding data is not included. UPDATED: When an RTP packet is received from the core network. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SENT_RTP_PACKETS (M803C2)
kpi_info.use: The number of sent RTP packets. The actual number of packets can be calculated by multiplying this counter value by 10. UPDATED: When an RTP packet is sent to the core network. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SENT_RTP_PAYLOAD (M803C3)
kpi_info.use: The RTP payload data sent during the measurement interval. Header and padding data is not included. UPDATED: When an RTP packet is sent to the core network. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: LOST_RTP_PACKETS (M803C4)
kpi_info.use: The number of lost ingress direction RTP data packets that are not received according to the received sequence numbers. This means that either the packet was lost in the Iu-CS transport or the packet arrived too late to the RTP buffer of RNC. Too late arrival can be caused by excessive jitter in the transport path. UPDATED:When an RTP packet is detected to be missing. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SENT_RTCP_PACKETS (M803C5)
kpi_info.use: The number of sent RTCP Sender and Receiver Reports. UPDATED:When an RTCP packet containing Sender or Receiver Report is sent to the core network. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REC_RTCP_PACKETS (M803C6)
kpi_info.use: The number of received RTCP Sender and Receiver Reports. UPDATED:When an RTCP packet containing Sender or Receiver Report is received from the core network. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RTP_JITTER_CLASS_1 (M803C7)
kpi_info.use: The number of 5 second sampling intervals where the average ingress direction RTP jitter in the Iu-CS interface is below 1 ms. UPDATED:The jitter is sampled with 5 second intervals for each RTP connection. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

UPDATED:The jitter is sampled with 5 second intervals for each RTP connection. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: LOST_EGRESS_RTP_PACKETS (M803C28)
kpi_info.use: The number of lost egress direction RTP data packets that are reported to be missing by MGW using RTCP protocol messages. This counter is supported only if RTCP protocol usage is enabled in the Iu-CS interface using IUCS object parameter RtcpActivation. UPDATED: When the RNC receives information from MGW via RTCP messages that egress direction RTP packets are missing. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.
